SCABIES - MEXICO: (VERACRUZ)
****************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 14 Dec 2011
Source: E Consulta [in Spanish, trans. Mod.JG, edited]


Veracruz healthcare services (SESVER) has stopped an outbreak of
scabies in Coscomatepec municipality. Health workers went home-by-home
to give curative therapy and preventive measures to every household in
the community after 426 cases of scabies were reported in 426
inhabitants in Tenixtepec community.

Local health authorities pointed out that no complications or deaths
due to scabies were reported after the administration of curative
therapy and preventive measures.

Eleven physicians, 3 nurses, 3 health care technicians, 11 health
promoters, 10 units from the vector control area, 4 units from the
sanitary risk protection division and personnel from the Municipal
System for Family Protection and Development participated in the
aforementioned campaign.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[Scabies is very contagious, and, if introduced in societies where
people are close together, it will spread rapidly. This is well known
in health care settings but unusual in the community. When people
present with severe itching, scabies should always be considered.

For the HealthMap of the location of this outbreak, see:
http://healthmap.org/r/1xvV. - Mod.EP]
